HEADWORD: Convellent
<hw>Con*vel"lent</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>convellens</ets>, p. pr. of <ets>convellere</ets>. See
<er>Convulse</er>.]</ety> <def>Tending to tear or pull up.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The ends of the fragment . . . will not yield to the
<qex>convellent</qex> force.</q> <rj><qau>Todd & Bowman.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Convenable</ent>⟦br⟧
